Gauteng police on Sunday confirmed a man was assaulted by community members in Slovo, Eldorado Park, for allegedly stealing cables and a car battery. A man in his 20s was arrested by the community after his was found in possession of the stolen goods. “The people have assaulted a man they are accusing of stealing a cable and car battery. When I attend the case, I found that there were so many people then I called for backup. An ambulance was called to take him to the hospital because he was badly injured,” Captain Chauke said. Another case mob justice is also being investigated in Eldorado Park after two men were beaten up by the community for allegedly kidnapping a young girl. The pair were taken to nearby hospitals and two members were taken to police station for questioning. The police have said there’s no evidence of kidnapping. -TNA Reporter